The paper discusses a novel differential equation-based modeling approach to understand the rapid growth of a journal in a niche area. This involves knowledge discovery from big data-centric methods, which suggests a focus on data science (cs.DS) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of delay differential equations to model the change in influence on a journal's status suggests a focus on cybernetics (cs.CY) and database systems (cs.DB). Additionally, the paper discusses the niche prominence of Astronomy and Computing, which suggests a focus on scientific computing (cs.SI).
